{
  "name": "Nexus-Director-Budget-Guardrails",
  "description": "Strict token-budgeting and clean architecture constraints for cost-effective iPadOS development.",
  "settings": {
    "prefer_model": "deepseek-v4-pro",
    "temperature": 0.1
  },
  "rules": [
    {
      "id": "cost_routing_ethic",
      "rule": "Default to DeepSeek for 90% of development work. All heavy backend logic, database schemas, utility functions, routes, and JSON parsing algorithms must be written using the most token-efficient code paths. Do not use premium models (like Claude or OpenAI) for basic boilerplate, math, or logical transformations."
    },
    {
      "id": "premium_token_reservation",
      "rule": "Reserve Claude tokens strictly for complex frontend visual layouts where visual intuition is mandatory. Reserve Gemini tokens exclusively for multi-modal parsing (raw video/audio streams) inside server endpoints. Never call these models for generic logic."
    },
    {
      "id": "prevent_functional_regressions",
      "rule": "Maintain strict architectural boundaries. All AI orchestration, prompt strings, and API drivers must live strictly inside the server-side directories (`/app/api/*`). Frontend TSX components must remain pure presentation layers that read state from endpoints. Never pollute the UI files with backend or model logic—this prevents visual regressions and wasted debugging tokens."
    },
    {
      "id": "ipados_safeguards",
      "rule": "All generated UI must adhere to iPad mobile Safari ergonomics to avoid wasting tokens rewriting broken layouts: 1. Always use dynamic viewports (`h-dvh`, `max-h-dvh`) instead of legacy `h-screen`. 2. Interactive text fields must have a minimum font size of `text-base` (16px) to block iOS auto-zooming. 3. Tap targets must be at least 48x48px with clear pointer-coarse hit areas. 4. Never hide critical actions behind hover-only (`hover:`) states."
    },
    {
      "id": "fail_fast_and_validate",
      "rule": "Enforce deterministic outputs. Always validate incoming AI payloads using Zod schemas and `generateObject`. Write comprehensive, defensive error handling and circuit breakers on the backend so API failures do not cause infinite loops, hung requests, or wasted tokens."
    },
    {
      "id": "code_generation_discipline",
      "rule": "Do not rewrite entire files for minor changes. Only output the specific modified functions or lines needed. When responding, skip verbose conversational filler and output clean, directly applicable code blocks to save prompt and completion token counts."
    }
  ]
}
For this specific project, I am working with limited bandwidth and need to adhere to strict developer guidelines to keep our workflow efficient. Please adopt the following project standards for all your responses:

Surgical Diffs: When I ask you to update a file, please do not rewrite the entire file. Only provide the exact block of code to remove and the exact new block to replace it with.
Code-Only Output: Please omit conversational filler, apologies, or explanations unless I specifically ask for them. Just outputting the raw code or diff is perfect.
Scoped Analysis: I will provide or @-mention the specific files we are working on. Please limit your analysis strictly to those files to save us both time.
Pause on Errors: If we are debugging and your suggested fix throws an error, please halt and wait for my input rather than attempting multiple automated retries.
Thank you for adopting these workflow standards for this workspace!